  "posts": [
    {
      "id": "PopularPost194366",
      "post_content": "[Merfolk Looter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Merfolk Looter)/[Reckless Scholar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reckless Scholar)/[Cephalid Looter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cephalid Looter)/[Looter Il-Kor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Looter Il-Kor)/[Riddlesmith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Riddlesmith) are good cards. If you have 3 or more cards in hand, being able to cycle 1 or 2 of them to smooth out your draws each turn is a powerful effect.   \n  \n[Jace, the Mind Sculptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor) was a powerful card for his ability to \"[Brainstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm)\" every turn, but his usefulness doubled with the aid of fetchlands to shuffle away useless cards you just placed on top of your library, otherwise he was basically a fancy **Swiss Army** [Scroll Rack](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scroll Rack) (*still a powerful card*). All these cards do is give you new cards, guaranteed, no questions asked. They don't provide card advantage, but they do offer card quality, a subtle yet powerful concept.",
      "posted_by": "DacenOctavio",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost194366\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\"><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Merfolk Looter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Merfolk Looter\">Merfolk Looter</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reckless Scholar\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reckless Scholar\">Reckless Scholar</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cephalid Looter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cephalid Looter\">Cephalid Looter</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Looter Il-Kor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Looter Il-Kor\">Looter Il-Kor</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Riddlesmith\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Riddlesmith\">Riddlesmith</a> are good cards. If you have 3 or more cards in hand, being able to cycle 1 or 2 of them to smooth out your draws each turn is a powerful effect. <br/><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Jace, the Mind Sculptor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor\">Jace, the Mind Sculptor</a> was a powerful card for his ability to \"<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Brainstorm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm\">Brainstorm</a>\" every turn, but his usefulness doubled with the aid of fetchlands to shuffle away useless cards you just placed on top of your library, otherwise he was basically a fancy <b>Swiss Army</b> <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Scroll Rack\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scroll Rack\">Scroll Rack</a> (<i>still a powerful card</i>). All these cards do is give you new cards, guaranteed, no questions asked. They  don't provide card advantage, but they do offer card quality, a subtle yet powerful concept.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '194366'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy2792\">DacenOctavio</span>\r\n                                (9/7/2011 8:38:16 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
